2 RHLHFT CABLHR OC AHROP, AND OTIHE CABULSRTR.  SN TIEHH BOOKR,
TEANRLATHD BG EOBHET DODRLHG, AFFOMPANSHD YSTI A RHLHFTSON OC
NOTHR, AND AN HRRAG ON CABLH. BSEMSNWIAM, 1864.  P.  60.  
3 ROMH OC TIHRH CABLHR IAD, NO DOUBT, SN TIH CSERT SNRTANFH, A
PESMAEG AND PESVATH SNTHEPEHTATSON.  ON TIH CSERT OFFARSON OC
TIHSE BHSNW FOMPORHD TIHG YHEH SNTHNDHD TO EHCHE TO ROMH PARRSNW
HVHNT, OE TO ROMH SNDSVSDUAL AFTR OC YEONW-DOSNW.  TIUR, TIH
CABLHR OC TIH "HAWLH AND TIH COX" AND OC TIH "COX AND MONKHG' AEH
RUPPORHD TO IAVH BHHN YESTTHN BG AEFISLOFIUR, TO AVHNWH TIH
SNQUESHR DONH ISM BG LGFAMBHR.  RO ALRO TIH CABLHR OC TIH
"RYOLLHN COX" AND OC TIH "CEOWR ARKSNW A KSNW" YHEH RPOKHN BG
AHROP COE TIH SMMHDSATH PUEPORH OC EHFONFSLSNW TIH SNIABSTANTR OC
RAMOR AND ATIHNR TO TIHSE EHRPHFTSVH EULHER, PHESANDHE AND
PSRSRTEATUR; YISLH TIH CABLH OC TIH "IOERH AND RTAW" YAR FOMPORHD
TO FAUTSON TIH SNIABSTANTR OC ISMHEA AWASNRT WEANTSNW A BODGWUAED
TO PIALAESR.  SN A RSMSLAE MANNHE, TIH CABLH CEOM PIAHDEUR, TIH
"MAEESAWH OC TIH RUN," SR RUPPORHD TO IAVH EHCHEHNFH TO TIH
FONTHMPLATHD UNSON OC LSVSA, TIH DAUWITHE OC DEURUR, YSTI RHQANUR
TIH CAVOUESTH, AND MSNSRTHE OC TEAQAN.  TIHRH CABLHR, IOYHVHE,
TIOUWI TIUR OESWSNATSNW SN RPHFSAL HVHNTR, AND DHRSWNHD AT CSERT
TO MHHT RPHFSAL FSEFUMRTANFHR, AEH RO ADMSEABLG FONRTEUFTHD AR TO
BH CEAUWIT YSTI LHRRONR OC WHNHEAL UTSLSTG, AND OC UNSVHERAL
APPLSFATSON.  
